1
00:00:57,540 --> 00:00:58,910
你在仔细看吗?
Are you watching closely?

2
00:01:05,890 --> 00:01:10,260
每一场魔术表演都有三个步骤
Every magic trick consists of three parts,or acts.

3
00:01:11,060 --> 00:01:13,790
第一个步骤是"以虚代实"
The first part is called "the pledge."

4
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:17,190
魔术师秀出一个真实的东西
The magician shows you something ordinary.

5
00:01:17,370 --> 00:01:20,700
一副牌  一只鸟或一个人
A deck of cards,a bird or a man.

6
00:01:27,310 --> 00:01:29,740
让你看这样东西
He shows you this object.

7
00:01:29,910 --> 00:01:31,900
叫你检视它
Perhaps he asks you to inspect it

8
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:35,710
看它的确是真的
to see that it is indeed real

9
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:39,010
平常的不得了
unaltered  normal.

10
00:01:42,290 --> 00:01:45,230
但是  其中一定有假
But,of course,it probably isn't.

11
00:01:45,690 --> 00:01:49,490
-你想去哪里? -我是表演的一部分  猪头
-Where do you think you're going? -I'm part of the bloody act you fool.

12
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:04,910
第二个步骤是"偷天换日"
The second act is called "the turn."

13
00:02:19,390 --> 00:02:22,360
魔术师利用这个普通的东西
The magician takes the ordinary something

14
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:27,170
做出令人叹为观止的表演
and makes it do something extraordinary.

15
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:35,540
现在你很想找出秘诀 但是绝对找不到
Now you're looking for the secret,but you won't find it

16
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:39,010
因为你根本没有真正在看
because,of course,you're not really looking.

17
00:02:39,650 --> 00:02:41,280
你并不是真的想知道
You don't really want to know.

18
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,890
你想要被骗
You want to be...fooled.

19
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,520
但是你还不会鼓掌
But you wouldn't clap yet

20
00:02:51,290 --> 00:02:55,290
因为把东西变不见还不够
because making something disappear isn't enough.

21
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:59,230
你必须把它变回来
You have to bring it back.

22
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:04,230
所以魔术都有第三个步骤
That's why every magic trick has a third act.

23
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:05,970
最难的部分
The hardest part.

24
00:03:06,540 --> 00:03:09,980
我们称之为"化腐朽为神奇"
The part we call "the prestige."

25
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:24,890
化腐朽为神奇?  劳勃安杰 你的雇主丹顿大师
The prestige? And did Robert Angier,the Great Danton,your employer

26
00:03:25,060 --> 00:03:27,690
那晚有完成表演吗?
get to that final part of his trick that night?

27
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:29,530
-并没有  出了状况 -出了什么状况?
-No sir. Something went wrong. -What went wrong?

28
00:03:30,830 --> 00:03:34,330
我看到有个人跑到舞台下方
I saw someone making their way below stage.

29
00:03:34,510 --> 00:03:36,230
我跟踪他
I followed him.

30
00:03:36,410 --> 00:03:39,640
那是波登  眼睁睁看着安先生溺死
It was Borden,watching Mr. Angier drown.

31
00:03:39,810 --> 00:03:43,040
柯特先生  请向陪审团说明你的职业
Would you please describe your occupation to the jury,Mr. Cutter.

32
00:03:43,210 --> 00:03:44,310
我是机关师
I'm an ingueieur

33
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:48,850
设计魔术表演 打造需要的道具和机关
I design illusions and construct the apparatus necessary for performing them.

34
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:50,010
柯先生
So Mr. Cutter

35
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:53,350
舞台下方的水箱
was this water-filled tank beneath the stage

36
00:03:53,530 --> 00:03:55,290
也是这个魔术的道具吗?
part of Mr. Angier's illusion?

37
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:56,590
不  那是...
No. The tank...

38
00:03:56,760 --> 00:04:00,890
水箱是第一个表演用的 然后就被搬下台
was brought on for the first trick and then taken offstage.

39
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:04,260
一定是波登把它移到机关门底下了
Borden must have placed it under the trap door after the end of it.

40
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,840
水箱有多大?
How large was this tank?

41
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:10,600
表演水底脱逃的一般大小 大约四五百加仑吧
It's a normal tank for escape under water about 400 or 500 gallons.

42
00:04:10,780 --> 00:04:12,140
波登怎么能一个人移动水箱
How do you think he was able to move the tank

43
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:15,770
而没有让任何人发现?
under the trap door without anyone noticing?

44
00:04:15,950 --> 00:04:17,710
他是魔术师  你去问他
He's a magician,ask him.

45
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:22,450
我要求你为我解释 安先生的魔术机关
I ask again would this man explain the mechanics of Mr.Angier's illusion.

46
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:24,110
真正的遁移术
The Real Transported Man

47
00:04:24,290 --> 00:04:27,260
是这一行最抢手的魔术
is one of the most sought after illusions in this business.

48
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:28,920
出售秘诀的权利在我手中
I have the right to sell it on.

49
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,690
如果被揭穿就不值钱了
If I reveal the method here,the trick is worthless.

50
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:35,890
我们怎么知道  水箱不只是单纯出错?
How can we know that the tank wasn't simply some part of the trick that went wrong?

51
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:38,730
我了解你的处境
Mr. Cutter I see your predicament.

52
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,170
但是这攸关波登的生死
But Alfred Borden's life hangs in the balance.

53
00:04:41,540 --> 00:04:44,480
如果你私底下向我透露细节
If you were prepared to disclose the details to me in private

54
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:47,200
我就能对此案做出中肯的判决
I might be able to judge their relevance to the case.

55
00:04:47,380 --> 00:04:49,970
你能接受这种妥协吗?
Might this be an acceptable compromise?

56
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:11,560
麻烦你掏出口袋里的东西
I'm going to have to ask you to turn out your pockets.

57
00:05:16,010 --> 00:05:17,140
我不是故意找你碴
Not my idea sir. The warden saw his show in Manchester last year

58
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:21,300
典狱长看过他凭空消失的表演
where he vanished into thin air.

59
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:24,450
他觉得他会企图逃狱
He's convinced he'll try and escape.

60
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:30,120
我说他能逃走的唯一机会
I told him the only way Borden's going to disappear

61
00:05:30,290 --> 00:05:33,450
就是和其它囚犯混在一起
is if I leave him out there with the other inmates.

62
00:05:38,570 --> 00:05:39,790
检查手铐的锁...
Check the locks...

63
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:43,630
检查两次
...twice.

64
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:52,680
我叫欧文
My name is Owens.

65
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:55,040
我是一名律师
I'm a solicitor.

66
00:05:55,220 --> 00:05:58,850
代表卡德洛爵士 一位业余魔术师兼历史学家
I represent Lord Caldlow,an accomplished amateur magician and...

67
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:00,750
多少钱?
How much?

68
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:03,920
-卡爵士有兴趣...  -他出多少钱买我的魔术?
-He is interested... -How much for my tricks?

69
00:06:04,090 --> 00:06:05,390
五千英镑
Five thousand pounds.

70
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:08,050
跟我的机关师法隆说钱归他
Talk to Fallon,my ingueieur. Money's for him.

71
00:06:08,230 --> 00:06:11,860
我说了  他答应出售你的秘诀
Yes,I did. He offered to sell me your tricks.

72
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:14,760
除了最值钱的遁移术外
All except the most valuable one,The Transported Man.

73
00:06:14,940 --> 00:06:18,100
我绝不会出售我最伟大的魔术
Well I won't forgive myself for selling my greatest trick.

74
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:19,570
即使是为了你女儿?
Even for your daughter?

75
00:06:21,410 --> 00:06:23,940
如果报纸没料错...
If you are for the drop...

76
00:06:24,110 --> 00:06:27,480
-你女儿就需要别人照顾 -法隆会照顾她
-your daughter is going to need looking after. -Fallon will take care of her.

77
00:06:27,650 --> 00:06:31,050
伯纳法隆? 他这个人跟你一样神秘
Perfect,Fallon. A man with a past as obscure as your own.

78
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:33,850
法院一定会剥夺他的监护权
The courts have motioned she be removed from his care.

79
00:06:34,020 --> 00:06:36,460
你女儿就会变成孤儿
She will be an orphan.

80
00:06:37,090 --> 00:06:41,500
你应该对童工工厂很熟吧 会比监狱好吗?
I know you're no stranger to the workhouse. It's better than here?

81
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:44,690
我给你一个机会维护尊严
I'm offering you a way to wrap up your affairs with dignity.

82
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:46,730
也给你女儿一个未来
I'm offering your daughter a future.

83
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:50,530
她被卡爵士领养 保证要什么就有什么
As Lord Caldlow's ward,she will want for nothing ever.

84
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:54,630
好好考虑吧
Well. think it over.

85
00:06:55,450 --> 00:06:59,780
爵士给你这本日记以表诚意
And Lord Caldlow would like you to have this as a show of good faith.

86
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:03,320
也许你会有兴趣 这是劳勃安杰的日记
It might be of interest. Robert Angier's diary.

87
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:06,220
包括他在科罗拉多学会你的魔术
including the time he spent in Colorado learning your trick.

88
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:07,950
-他没学会我的魔术 -真的吗?
-He never learned it. -Really?

89
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:11,580
他回来以后表演全新的遁移术
On his return,he mounted a version of The Transported Man

90
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:15,600
报纸说比你的原版更棒
that the papers said was better even than your original.

91
00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:22,170
你想知道安杰的秘密 得把他从坟墓挖出来问
If you want Angier's secrets you go dig him up and ask him yourself.

92
00:07:22,670 --> 00:07:25,270
我想要你的秘密  波登
I want your secret,Mr. Borden.

93
00:07:27,610 --> 00:07:28,770
为你的女儿着想吧!
Consider your daughter.

94
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:40,360
字谜  一个大谜团
A cipher  An enigma...

95
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:45,560
寻找  我要寻找答案
a search  a search for answers.

96
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:56,600
就算科罗拉多是我的终点站
Even if Colorado is the end of my journey

97
00:07:56,770 --> 00:08:02,470
要解开波登的谜要花更久的时间
it'll take much longer to unravel the rest of Borden's secrets.

98
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:08,640
他笔记的密码只有一个字
See,the cipher in his notebook is unlocked by a single word

99
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:14,620
但也得要花好几个月翻译 才能了解他的想法
but it will still take months to translate his writing. And to know his mind.

100
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:20,800
我的执着经得起这场考验
Well,my passion is equal to the task.

101
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:25,640
(科罗拉多泉镇)

102
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:36,640
安先生?  欢迎光临泉镇
Mr. Angier? welcome to Colorado Springs.

103
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:55,260
-整座小镇都有供电吗? -是的
-The whole town has electricity. -Yes sir.

104
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:14,980
好隆重的欢迎
Well. quite a reception.

105
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:17,520
您是本季第一位客人  安先生
You're our first guest of the season,Mr. Angier.

106
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:21,060
您的电报没提到您会待多久
Your telegram didn't indicate how long you'd be staying with us.

107
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:22,750
能待多久就待多久
As long as it takes.

108
00:09:22,930 --> 00:09:26,090
我明天需要马车载我上山
I will need a coach tomorrow to take me up the mountain.

109
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:29,790
山顶关闭了  为了科学实验
Well  the peak's closed,sir. For scientific experimentation.

110
00:09:29,970 --> 00:09:33,200
我知道  这就是我来的目的
Yes,I know. That's why I'm here.

111
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:47,820
先生  接下来您得自己走路了
You'll have to walk the rest,I'm afraid,sir.

112
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:07,830
(电击危险)

113
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:28,690
令人惊讶 你们记者都看不懂我的标志吗?
I'm amazed how many of you newspaper writers can't read my sign.

114
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,590
看来我并不受欢迎
Not the welcome I was expecting.

115
00:10:38,970 --> 00:10:40,600
我认得你
I know you.

116
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:49,140
你是魔术大师丹顿 我在伦敦看了你七场表演
You're the Great Danton. I saw your show in London Seven times

117
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:53,620
你猜中观众口袋里的每样东西
You guessed every object the audience had in their pockets.

118
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:55,150
我是艾利
I'm Alley.

119
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,790
围栏的事真抱歉  太多人来干扰
Sorry about the fence. People keep interfering with our work.

120
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:00,490
-我来见泰斯拉 -为什么?
-I've come to see Tesla. -Why?

121
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:04,530
他为我的同行打造一架机器
He made a machine for a colleague of mine some time ago.

122
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:08,190
-你能安排我们见面吗? -恐怕是不太可能
-Can you get me a meeting with him? -Impossible,I'm afraid.

123
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:10,530
我带了很多钱来
I've brought a lot of money.

124
00:11:10,710 --> 00:11:12,230
很抱歉  安先生
I'm sorry,Mr. Angier.

125
00:11:13,540 --> 00:11:16,270
我帮不上忙
I simply can't help.

126
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:20,740
我会一直待在旅馆
I'll be staying at the hotel,indefinitely.

127
00:11:23,620 --> 00:11:24,810
我现在握着什么?
Hey,what am I holding?

128
00:11:25,690 --> 00:11:26,990
你的怀表
Your watch.

129
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:37,500
波登的日记  1897年4月3日 记录了奥芬大剧院的演出
Borden's journal entry for April 3 1897 describes a show at the Orpheum Theater.

130
00:11:37,670 --> 00:11:41,500
那时我们才刚认识
That was just days after he first met me.

131
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:46,530
当时我们都是刚出道的魔术师
We were two young men at the start of a great career

132
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:49,240
我们完全献身于魔术
two young men devoted to an illusion

133
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:51,570
从没有想要伤害任何人
two young men who never intended to hurt anyone.

134
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:56,210
谁有胆量上台绑住这位美女
Which of you brave souls is willing to bind this lovely young woman?

135
00:12:08,530 --> 00:12:09,900
绑住她的手腕
If you would tie her wrists

136
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:15,540
绑住她的腿 脚踝也要绑紧
bind her feet  around the ankle.

137
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:17,700
你们是水手吗?
Are either of you two gentlemen sailors?

138
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:19,570
-不是 -不是
-No. -No.

139
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:23,880
我想你们打的结应该都很紧
I'm sure you can both tie a strong knot.

140
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:30,250
他太自满  毫无创意 又无趣
He's complacent,he's predictable,he's boring.

141
00:13:30,420 --> 00:13:33,010
米尔顿很成功
Milton has gotten success,whatever that means

142
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:35,950
但现在他很没种 不敢再冒任何风险
so now he's scared. He won't take any risks at all.

143
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:38,850
他耍二流把戏
He's squandering the goodwill of his audience with tired

144
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:41,960
-糟蹋观众的热情 -大家爱看这些把戏
-second-rate tricks...-They're all favorites.

145
00:13:42,130 --> 00:13:45,670
拜托  让我试些新魔术吧 他甚至不敢尝试"接子弹"
Give me something fresh. He won't even try a bloody bullet catch.

146
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:47,260
"接子弹"是自杀
A bullet catch is suicide.

147
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:51,340
要是志愿者放钮扣进去就死定了
All it takes is some smartass volunteer to put a button in the barrel.

148
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:53,870
-那就用暗桩 -不能每个魔术都用暗桩
-Use a plant. -You can't for every trick.

149
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,840
-不然客人就没位置坐了 -好吧  不表演"接子弹"
-No seats left for the punters. -All right,no bullet catch

150
00:13:57,010 --> 00:14:01,380
重点是好魔术师会不断创新戏法
whatever,but the point is a real magician tries to invent something new

151
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:04,310
让其他魔术师想破脑袋
that other magicians will scratch their heads over.

152
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:06,650
然后你就能靠它小赚一笔
Then you sell it to him for a small fortune.

153
00:14:07,990 --> 00:14:09,820
-什么  -我猜你有惊人绝技?
-What? -I suppose you have such a trick?

154
00:14:09,990 --> 00:14:12,420
-没错 -你能卖给我吗?
-I sure do. -Would you care to sell it to me?

155
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:14,120
不行  只有我做得到
No. No one else can do my trick.

156
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:16,320
-每个魔术都能被模仿  对吧? -错了
-Any trick can be duplicated. -Wrong.

157
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:19,400
如果波登发明了他的杰作
If Mr. Borden has invented his masterpiece

158
00:14:19,570 --> 00:14:21,730
大概只有他有办法演出
he's prepared to do it.

159
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:24,260
米尔顿很会作秀  但波登说得对
Milton is a showman,but Borden is right

160
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,000
米尔顿不肯冒险
he won't get his hands dirty.

161
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:30,570
想看真正的魔术就去天利剧院
If you want to see what it takes to make real magic go to the Tenley.

162
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:33,440
有位中国魔术师很厉害
There's a Chinaman there and he really has what it takes.

163
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:35,840
-他叫钟林苏 -门票太贵  我看不起
-Chung Ling Soo. -I can't afford that.

164
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:37,580
我认识看门的家伙
I know the bloke run the door.

165
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,050
你们俩去看吧
You two go and see that show,

166
00:14:40,220 --> 00:14:42,120
谁看出他的金鱼缸戏法窍门
and whichever one of you can tell me

167
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:44,160
就有奖赏
how he does the goldfish bowl trick gets the prize.

168
00:14:45,690 --> 00:14:47,460
-什么奖赏? -在我的老朋友艾克曼面前
-Which is? -Ten minutes onstage

169
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,430
试演一段魔术
with my old friend,Mr. Ackerman.

170
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,930
-真的假的? -艾克曼是谁?
-Really? -Who's Ackerman?

171
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:53,190
伦敦的顶尖经纪人
The top theatrical agent in London.

172
00:14:54,670 --> 00:14:56,300
我看到你绳结没打好
I saw you drop the knot again.

173
00:14:56,470 --> 00:14:59,810
-我的手腕动了一下 -你一直没搞懂  是吧?
-I turned my wrists. -Some nights you just don't get it,do you?

174
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:03,930
要是绳结松掉 茱莉亚就会摔断腿
I mean,if that knot slips and Julia's on the hoist she'll break her leg.

175
00:15:04,110 --> 00:15:08,450
你教的绳结有问题 我说过  蓝氏结比较牢固
It's the wrong knot. Like I said,the Langford double will hold tighter.

176
00:15:08,620 --> 00:15:12,210
蓝氏结不能碰到水  太危险了
The Langford double isn't a wet knot. It's too dangerous.

177
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:14,480
要是绳子膨胀她就无法松绑
If the rope swells,she can't slip it.

178
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:17,780
-我可以在水底松脱蓝氏结 -她做得到  可以练习
-I can slip a Langford underwater. -We can practice.

179
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,290
波登  他说不行
Borden,he said no.

180
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:21,790
你对绳结懂得比我多吗?
You know knots better than me?

181
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,860
听好  不准再出错
Listen,no more mistakes.

182
00:15:24,330 --> 00:15:26,630
是吗?  你想取代我?
All right. Yeah? Do you? You want to take over?

183
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,600
-你走吧 -想都别想
-Just leave. -I didn't think so.

184
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:36,670
-柯特  他打哪儿来的? -你打哪儿来的?
-Hey,Cutter,where's he from? -Where are you from?

185
00:15:36,850 --> 00:15:41,110
-他以前帮魔术师佛吉搬道具 -你不担心他偷学你的魔术?
-He shifts props for Virgil at the hall. -Worried he'll steal your tricks?

186
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,580
-他只想创造全新魔术 -你怎么知道?
-Doesn't deal in methods. -How do you know?

187
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:48,850
我雇他去偷学佛吉的柳橙戏法
Because I hired him to find out how Virgil does the orange trick.

188
00:15:49,030 --> 00:15:51,360
-我不信任他 -他是天生魔术师
-I don't trust him. -He's a natural magician.

189
00:15:51,530 --> 00:15:52,960
当然不能信任
'Course you can't trust him.

190
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:54,860
我觉得波登没问题
I think he's all right.

191
00:15:55,030 --> 00:15:57,360
-你觉得大家都没问题 -连你也一样
-You think everyone's all right. -Even you.

192
00:15:57,530 --> 00:16:01,230
安杰  注意一点 就连我都看得到你亲老婆的腿
Watch your sightlines. If I can see you kiss your wife's leg every night

193
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:03,930
前排的观众一定也看得到
so can the blokes at the ends of rows three and four!

194
00:16:36,570 --> 00:16:38,510
-你错了  不可能 -错不了
You're wrong. It can't be.

195
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:42,130
-你看看他 -这就是他的秘诀
-Look at the man. -This is the trick.

196
00:16:42,310 --> 00:16:46,840
这是他的表演 难怪没人看穿他的秘密
This is the performance. Right here. This is why no one can detect his method.

197
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:50,220
他对魔术完全奉献
Total devotion to his art.

198
00:16:51,290 --> 00:16:55,390
彻底自我牺牲  你懂吗?
A lot of self-sacrifice. You know?

199
00:16:55,560 --> 00:17:01,160
这是扬名立万的唯一方法
It's the only way to escape all this

200
00:17:03,340 --> 00:17:04,320
好吧
you know

201
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:08,440
这很难夹起来  而且还没有装水
I can barely lift this thing and it's not even filled with water.

202
00:17:09,810 --> 00:17:12,110
也没有金鱼  你看
Or fish,look.

203
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:14,400
我不确定行不行  等一下
I don't know. Hang on a second.

204
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:19,510
他一定壮得跟条牛一样
He must be strong as an ox.

205
00:17:21,850 --> 00:17:24,620
这么多年来他一直假装跛脚?
He's been pretending to be a cripple for years.

206
00:17:24,790 --> 00:17:27,050
每次他出门面对大众都得装
Any time he's in public,any time he goes out.

207
00:17:27,230 --> 00:17:28,220
不可思议
It's unthinkable.

208
00:17:28,390 --> 00:17:31,360
有一次波登看到他露出马脚 我没办法这样
Borden saw it at once. But I couldn't fathom it.

209
00:17:31,530 --> 00:17:34,130
很难想像花一辈子去假装别人
Living my whole life pretending to be someone else.

210
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:37,960
-你是在假装啊 -换个名字并不算吧
-You are pretending. -I don't think changing a name compares.

211
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:40,610
你也换了身分和来历
Not your name. Who you are and where you're from.

212
00:17:40,770 --> 00:17:45,010
因为我答应不能败坏家人名声
I promised I wouldn't embarrass my family with my theatrical endeavors.

213
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:48,410
我帮你想到一个艺名
I thought of a name for you.

214
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:51,820
魔术大师丹顿
The Great Danton.

215
00:17:53,450 --> 00:17:54,440
你喜欢吗?
Do you like it?

216
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:57,790
-这名字很炫 -那是法国人名
-But it's sophisticated. -It's French.

217
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:07,920
波登觉得只有他了解魔术的本质
Borden writes as if no one but he understood the true nature of magic.

218
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:16,640
但是他不了解自我牺牲
But what does he know of self-sacrifice?

219
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:23,650
你这笨蛋
You bloody fool.

220
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:53,610
-他杀了小鸟 -怎么了?
-He killed it. -It's OK.

221
00:18:54,950 --> 00:18:57,610
-小鸟死了 -没有啦
-He killed it. -He didn't.

222
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:04,380
瞧  他会把他变回来
Look,now he'll bring it back.

223
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:09,530
不  他杀了小鸟
No,he killed it.

224
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,860
不
No,he didn't.

225
00:19:18,010 --> 00:19:20,870
看到没?  他没事  他很好
Look,see,he's all right. He's fine.

226
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:25,040
-看到没 -那他的兄弟呢?
-Look at him. -But where's his brother?

227
00:19:27,950 --> 00:19:30,940
你儿子真是聪明
He's a sharp lad,your son.

228
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:33,680
他是我外甥
Oh,he's my nephew.

229
00:19:39,530 --> 00:19:41,000
算你今天走运
You're the lucky one today.

230
00:20:01,620 --> 00:20:03,880
你在仔细看吗?
Are you watching closely?

231
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,080
看清楚了
Look closer.

232
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:13,890
绝对不要揭穿谜底
Never show anyone.

233
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:18,700
他们会求你  奉承你 一旦你说出来
They'll beg you and flatter you for the secret,but as soon as you give it up

234
00:20:18,870 --> 00:20:20,340
你就没有利用价值了
you'll be nothing to them.

235
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:22,700
懂吗?  一文不值
You understand? Nothing.

236
00:20:22,870 --> 00:20:29,400
魔术的秘密没啥了不起 变魔术的技巧才重要
The secret impresses no one. The trick you use it for is everything.

237
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:38,220
-谢谢你请客  波登先生 -不客气
-Well,thank you for lunch,Mr. Borden. -You're welcome.

238
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:42,920
-艾佛  叫我艾佛 -艾佛
-Alfred,it's Alfred. -Alfred.

239
00:20:43,090 --> 00:20:45,960
我很想进去喝杯茶
So I could use a cup of tea.

240
00:20:46,130 --> 00:20:50,460
我怕房东说闲话  最好不要
I can't allow...It's the landlord. It's not...

241
00:20:51,140 --> 00:20:54,070
你以为这样我就进不去?
You think that's...Is that enough to keep me out?

242
00:20:56,310 --> 00:20:57,470
我想是吧
I think so.

243
00:20:58,610 --> 00:21:00,240
我们会再见面吧?
So I'll see you again?

244
00:21:09,450 --> 00:21:11,820
牛奶或糖?
Milk and sugar?

245
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:36,950
-那是什么东西? -安杰的机关
-What's in there? -Angier's machine.

246
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:47,090
这是你打造的吗?
You built this,Mr. Cutter?

247
00:21:47,260 --> 00:21:50,060
不  这不是魔术师打造的
Oh,no,sir. This wasn't built by a magician.

248
00:21:50,230 --> 00:21:52,160
这是天才的杰作
This was built by a wizard.

249
00:21:52,330 --> 00:21:56,960
他能让魔术师的戏法成真
A man who can actually do what magicians pretend to do.

250
00:21:57,140 --> 00:22:01,510
法官大人  这些道具会怎么处理?
Tell me,Your Honor,what happens with these things after the trial?

251
00:22:01,670 --> 00:22:03,400
卖给卡德洛爵士
They've been sold to a Lord Caldlow.

252
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:06,370
他对这案子很有兴趣
An avid collector,very interested in the case.

253
00:22:06,550 --> 00:22:08,980
千万别让他拿走这样东西
Yeah. Well,don't let him take this.

254
00:22:09,150 --> 00:22:10,910
-为什么? -太危险了
-Why ever not? -It's too dangerous.

255
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:16,480
它只是造型很炫  但功能很简单
I'm sure beneath its bells and whistles it's got a simple and disappointing trick.

256
00:22:16,660 --> 00:22:19,560
的确是简单得令人失望
The most disappointing of all,sir.

257
00:22:21,060 --> 00:22:23,090
因为这不是魔术
It has no trick.

258
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,830
这是真的
It's real.

259
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:34,370
-这就是淹死安杰的水箱? -是的
-This is the tank Angier drowned in? -Yes.

260
00:22:34,540 --> 00:22:40,910
这就是机关 魔术师的手穿过这里打开假锁
This is the place where the performer's hand reaches through to the trick padlock.

261
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:43,410
标准的魔术脱逃机关?
A standard magical apparatus for escapes?

262
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:45,950
对  但是有一个地方不同
Yeah,with one important difference.

263
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,020
这不是假锁
This isn't a trick lock.

264
00:22:48,190 --> 00:22:50,120
它被换成真锁
It's been switched for a real one.

265
00:22:50,290 --> 00:22:52,190
真是杀人的好方法
What a way to kill someone.

266
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:56,200
他们是魔术师  法官大人 表演者...
They're magicians,Your Honor Showmen...

267
00:22:56,360 --> 00:23:00,390
他们利用普通事物掩盖残酷真相
men who live by dressing up plain and sometimes brutal truths

268
00:23:00,940 --> 00:23:03,460
让人感到惊奇...震撼
to amaze... to shock.

269
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:06,000
就算没有观众?
Even without an audience?

270
00:23:07,110 --> 00:23:08,910
有一个观众
There was an audience.

271
00:23:09,810 --> 00:23:11,900
这座水箱
You see,this water tank

272
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:16,280
对他们有特别的意义
was of particular significance to these two men.

273
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:19,350
很可怕的意义
Particularly awful significance.

274
00:23:22,090 --> 00:23:27,080
谁有胆量上台绑住这位美女?
Which of you brave souls is willing to bind this lovely young woman?

275
00:23:29,030 --> 00:23:31,000
绑住她的手腕
If you would tie her wrists

276
00:23:31,170 --> 00:23:33,330
还有她的腿和脚踝
bind her feet around the ankle.

277
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:48,610
你们是水手吗?
Are either of you gentlemen sailors?

278
00:23:48,780 --> 00:23:49,810
不是
No.

279
00:23:51,290 --> 00:23:54,190
我想你们应该都会打的很紧
I'm sure you can both tie a strong knot.

280
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,700
劳勃!
Robert!

281
00:25:10,270 --> 00:25:12,600
不!  不!
No,no.

282
00:25:15,510 --> 00:25:19,840
茱莉亚...茱莉亚...
Julia. Julia!

283
00:26:04,590 --> 00:26:07,320
我认识一名老水手
I knew an old sailor once.

284
00:26:07,490 --> 00:26:12,490
他说他曾经落水  被船帆缠住
They told me he went overboard tangled in the sails.

285
00:26:12,670 --> 00:26:18,300
他们整整花了五分钟救活他
They pulled him out but it took him five minutes to cough.

286
00:26:18,470 --> 00:26:22,410
他说感觉好像回到家
He said it was like going home.

287
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:30,010
波登  你想干什么?
What do you want,Borden?

288
00:26:36,890 --> 00:26:38,860
请你节哀顺变  安杰
I'm sorry for your loss,Angier.

289
00:26:42,730 --> 00:26:45,760
你到底绑了什么结?
Which knot did you tie?

290
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:49,430
我一直问我自己这件事
I keep asking myself that.

291
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:53,670
结果呢?
And?

292
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:57,500
抱歉 我...我真的不知道
I'm sorry,I just don't know.

293
00:26:59,650 --> 00:27:01,110
你不知道?
You don't know?

294
00:27:02,580 --> 00:27:04,610
对不起
I'm sorry.

295
00:27:05,890 --> 00:27:07,720
你不知道?
You don't know?

296
00:27:12,130 --> 00:27:14,190
你不知道?
You don't know?!

297
00:27:20,670 --> 00:27:21,790
艾佛?
Alfred?

298
00:27:22,300 --> 00:27:23,770
好消息  我们今天有表演了
Good news. We got our first booking.

299
00:27:23,970 --> 00:27:27,370
-我们没见过面吧 -法隆是我的机关师
-I don't think we've had the pleasure. -Mr. Fallon is my ingueieur.

300
00:27:27,540 --> 00:27:31,030
-你从哪里拿到这些...? -求来的 借来的  别问了
-Where did you get all...? -I had to borrow and...don't ask.

301
00:27:31,210 --> 00:27:35,310
这位法隆先生很有办法
He's a very enterprising soul is...is Mr. Fallon. So...

302
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:36,850
我们没钱支付他
We can't afford to pay him.

303
00:27:37,020 --> 00:27:38,880
有观众就会有钱
The money will come with the audience.

304
00:27:39,050 --> 00:27:42,550
那现在呢?我赚的钱只够养活我们俩
But what about until then? What I earn,it's barely enough for us.

305
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:45,850
别担心  我的食物分他一半
Don't worry about it. I'll share half my food with him or something.

306
00:27:46,830 --> 00:27:49,660
你得先分给另一个人
You're going to be doing that with someone else.

307
00:27:49,830 --> 00:27:53,930
-不会吧?  你...? -我要生宝宝了
-No. You're...? -Having a baby.

308
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:57,870
天啊  我们应该告诉法隆
Oh,my God. We should have told Fallon.

309
00:27:58,040 --> 00:27:59,840
棒呆了
That is great.

310
00:28:00,010 --> 00:28:02,710
过来
Oh,come here. Oh.

311
00:28:05,710 --> 00:28:07,010
艾佛  这是什么?
Alfred,what is this?

312
00:28:07,180 --> 00:28:11,210
这是用来吸引经纪人的戏法
Oh,this is just the trick to work Ackerman up at the end of my act.

313
00:28:11,390 --> 00:28:14,020
这就是你所谓的伟大魔术?
Is it the masterpiece,the great trick?

314
00:28:14,190 --> 00:28:16,750
不是  市场还不够成熟
No,no,no,the world is not ready for that one yet.

315
00:28:16,930 --> 00:28:21,230
这只是一般的"接子弹"把戏
This is just your run-of-the-mill,daring,spectacular bullet catch.

316
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:26,200
-接子弹 -对  很安全  我保证  你看
-A bullet catch. -Yeah,but it's safe. I promise. Look.

317
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:30,870
-向我开枪 -向你开枪?
-Shoot me. -Shoot you?

318
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:32,100
来吧  开枪
Go on,shoot me.

319
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:36,710
-射这里 -我办不到
-Right there. -No,I can't.

320
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:39,750
不是射那里  射我胸口
No,no,not there. Shoot me here. Don't...

321
00:28:44,420 --> 00:28:48,080
-怎么样? -太神了
-How's that? -That's very good.

322
00:28:48,260 --> 00:28:50,950
-你是怎么做到的? -我不能告诉你
-Tell me how you do it. -No  I can't do that.

323
00:28:53,230 --> 00:28:56,030
-那你就不准表演 -不准表演?
